HEADWORD: Stapes
<hw>Sta"pes</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"p⟦emac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[LL., a stirrup.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The innermost of
the ossicles of the ear; the stirrup, or stirrup bone; -- so called from
its form. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Staphyline</ent>⟦br⟧
